#Total assets show a clear upward trend over time for both mutual and stock companies, with increasing variability in later years. A small number of firms hold significantly larger asset levels, contributing to the wider distributions observed in the boxplots.Bond ratios are consistently higher than stock ratios across both company types, indicating a stronger allocation toward bonds. Mutual companies tend to maintain slightly higher bond allocations, while stock companies show somewhat more variation in stock exposure. Overall, insurers appear to follow a relatively conservative investment strategy dominated by bonds.
